4) Because the background varies, your discovery sensitivity threshold (how many particles you would need to see) also varies. What is the '5-sigma' threshold for a 100 millisecond GRB at different times?

In [33]:
sig=stats.norm.sf(5)
five_counts=int(stats.poisson.isf(sig,5))
six_counts = int(stats.poisson.isf(sig,7))
print('For 5 counts, a 5 sigma threshold value is ' + str(five_counts))
print('For 6 counts, a 5 sigma threshold value is ' + str(six_counts))

For 5 counts, a 5 sigma threshold value is 20
For 6 counts, a 5 sigma threshold value is 24

average = []
ave=[]
for i in range(200):
    for j in range(200):
        for k in range(8):
            ave = np.mean(data[i,j,0])
            average.append(ave)
            
plt.hist(average, bins = 'auto');
plt.xlim(-5,10);
plt.yscale('log')
plt.title('Distribution')
plt.xlabel('Brightness')
plt.ylabel('Counts')
